The paper deals with the intersection and contact graphs of convex bodies, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of graphs and their properties is also relevant to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper uses techniques from graph theory (cs.GT) to prove its results. Finally, the paper discusses the application of its results to sensor networks (cs.SI).
